Task: 02
Title: Domain ports
Phase: 1
Route: full
Slice: Passthrough Chat Completion (OpenAI)
Dependencies: 01
Scope: Define the four outbound port interfaces in the domain layer: ChatModelPort (with complete() signature only — stream() added in Phase 3), ConfigPort, LoggerPort, and ClockPort. All ports reference only domain model types. These interfaces are the contracts that infrastructure adapters will implement and application use cases will consume.
Acceptance Criteria: AC-3 (partial — complete() signature)
NFRs: NFR-1
Gate Criteria: Phase 1 Gate 2 (zero SDK/framework imports in domain)
Files:
  - src/domain/ports/chat-model-port.ts (CREATE) — ChatModelPort interface with complete(request: ChatRequest): Promise<ChatResponse>; stream() deferred to Task 09
  - src/domain/ports/config-port.ts (CREATE) — ConfigPort interface: getPanelModels(), getJudgeModel(), getSynthesizerModel(), getTimeoutMs()
  - src/domain/ports/logger-port.ts (CREATE) — LoggerPort interface: logStageStart, logStageEnd, logFailedModels, logError
  - src/domain/ports/clock-port.ts (CREATE) — ClockPort interface: now(): number (wraps Date.now() for testability)
